            Madge who challenged her to write a story. The story begins when Hastings is sent back to England from the
            First World War due to injury and is invited to spend his sick leave at the beautiful Styles Court by his
            old friend John Cavendish. Here, Hastings meets John’s step-mother, Mrs Inglethorp, and her new husband,
            Alfred. Despite the tranquil surroundings Hastings begins to realise that all is not right. When Mrs
            Inglethorp is found poisoned, suspicion falls on the family, and another old friend, Hercule Poirot, is
